reviews_data.review_text: So calming. Holy Spirit is definitely here. ☺️

The service was great. So friendly and professional.  The coffee however was not worth the money. Really watery. Just poorly made. Not what I expected. Hate to say it but I can't spend that kind of money there again :(

First time visting . I wanted to love this place. I love the Christian theme . I just have to be honest . The coffee was just not very good. I ordered a small iced latte . It was FILLED with ice , and after 4 sips it was gone . It really tasted no different than a McDonald’s Iced coffee. The difference is the McDonald’s ice coffee is huge and 1 dollar. I paid over 8 dollars for this one drink! Very disappointed . The vibe is very nice , but for the cost to be more than Starbucks , the drink needs to be top notch.
Always great service and drinks as well as baked goods.
Nice spot for coffee

I recently visited Holy Grind Coffee Shop in Kannapolis and had a very uncomfortable experience. I was working from there with my daughter when I noticed an employee walking around with a gun holstered behind her back. While I understand people have the right to bear arms, seeing a weapon openly in a Christian coffee shop made both of us uneasy. I didn’t even realize she worked there at first, until I saw her staring at me and walking back and forth between the couches and behind the counter, even eating in between.

This was unsettling, and it took away  from the experience. I personally feel that a workplace like this should have clearer boundaries around weapons, especially when there are families and customers present.

To top it off, the banana and cream smoothie I ordered was disappointing. It tasted like a cup of crushed ice and milk with a faint taste of banana. I’ve been to the concord location and ordered the same thing and it was made much better. I also ordered a matcha latte, it was okay but tasted a bit watered down.

I was hoping for a nice, relaxing spot, but unfortunately, this visit did not meet expectations at all.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jaida,
We're sorry to hear about your negative experience. We will address it with our staff. We apologize that it made you and your daughter feel uncomfortable. 
I am one of the owners and I was here during that time. I'm sorry your drinks weren't satisfactory. I had a new employee that was training that day and she is still learning. We could have remade your drinks if we had been made aware of the situation. If you'd like to come back we will be more then happy to remake both of your drinks on us.

I use to get them at the concord location but they stopped selling them so now whenever I go to kannapolis to drop daughter off at her dads I make it a point to stop & get one at kannapolis location. Plz plz don’t stop making this flavor. Can’t get it literally anywhere else.

reviews_data.review_text: The best and cutest coffee shop ever! I am not someone who really even likes coffee, but I love it here! Also they have plenty of other options like smoothies, flavored lemonades, and there’s something for everyone!
The absolute best place ! coffee is always great ! Customer service is always amazing! I go to all locations but kannapolis is my favorite 💓

reviews_data.review_text: This was my first visit to Holy Grind Coffee after seeing it on TikTok. I loved the idea of a Christian coffee shop and was genuinely excited to support it. Unfortunately, the experience was disappointing. I ordered a caramel macchiato and ended up paying nearly $18, mainly because they charge extra for flavoring, which I found unusual. When I asked about it, the staff explained that their macchiatos don’t typically include flavor by default. I’ve been to many coffee shops, and that’s not the norm. Sadly, the coffee itself was weak and lacked flavor. I really wanted to like this place, but the drink just wasn’t worth the price. I won’t be returning.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Samone, 
Thank you for your feed back. I spoke with our staff. You were refunded for 2 macchiatos. Our macchiatos are different from most other shops because we have more product in ours and your flavoring would have been 
at the bottom of your drinks because its layered. We're sorry that you were unhappy with your order. Maybe a Latte would have been better for your flavor palate with more evenly dispersed flavoring. We'd love for you to give us another try as we have a large selection to choose from.

reviews_data.review_text: Drinks are great. Staff is always friendly. Great place to meet with friends or stop in for a office way from the office.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for the kind words and continued support! Hope to see you again soon

reviews_data.review_text: We came here a week ago and the service was a little slow despite no line or being busy, just full of people everyone just lounging on their laptops and scrolling on their phones. The danishes were great but the flavored iced coffee was very band with little to no flavor. We came back again today to give it another try and we sat at the drive through for at least 30 minutes with no one coming to take our order. I am out of the store this week but I will definitely address this with my staff pronto because I also don't understand.  I hope you will consider coming again.

reviews_data.review_text: I had heard about Holy Grind several times from my daughter and others with Genuine Team leaders in Kannapolis.   I drove by tonight and needed a warm place to wait for my daughter’s class to end at Genuine.     So decided to try out Holy Grind coffee for my first time.   The service was not very personable or friendly.  I understood that it was 40 minutes till closing so gave the benefit of doubt.  I sat down to try my coffee and realized I needed more mocha flavor because it didn’t have the right flavor    Just as I went to see the barista she went to the back getting ready to pack up for the night.   I asked for a tad bit more mocha flavor and she simply gave me 3 pumps of mocha which made it way to sweet.  So again in between customers asked for black coffee to be added to my mocha.   Then it still was too sweet.  Again I asked before leaving to have more black coffee.  Never once did she care or offer to remake the mocha for me.  She could have asked how many pumps I might needed since I asked for a bit more coffee.  She didn’t have the warm friendly attitude I thought this place would have.  It was disappointing for my first time.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Tanya, we apologize for your experience.  We encourage our staff in good customer service and to go above an beyond within reason. Thank you for bringing this to our attention and it will be addressed. We agree, it should have been remade for you after the 2nd request for adjustment. 
We'd love to serve you again and make a drink on us.

reviews_data.review_text:
1st time going here 8/24/24. I have always wanted to go but, never could find the time. So, Saturday we went. The Menu is impressive, and we were so excited. We pulled up to the 1st window and waited what felt like forever, with just one car in front of us, no signs saying stay here to order, no one at window. No one ever came to the 1st window, so we pulled up the 2nd window, and then one of the girls came to the window and then asked us to put the truck into reverse to the 1st window.  Yes, she seemed nice but, then you could feel the aggravation with us, and the other girl she was working with, and kept calling her name (that started with an A, to not put her name out there) and then we asked about pastries and she called for the other girl and never helped her and then went and checked she just seemed Very Frustrated.
Put our order in, and I guess to sit at 2nd window again for an extended time. Watching the (2 girls) talk to people at the front counter, and waited what felt like way too long for 2 drinks, and 2 Pastries. Then she shoved the boxed items out the window, and No thank you, No have a Nice day...Nothing. The coffees were OK (5/10), (all the syrup was at the bottom :/ even though you had to try to stir the iced one with the straw that kept bending which I recommend a stronger straw if such thing. The girl who ever she is could have made this better, but if they don't have enough help, or if the help isn't helping then this is what is going to happen every time.  The Friendly vibe wasn't there and what she tried just felt like attitude when we had questions.

Long Wait time, Not Friendly, Over Priced for Just OK Coffee, and attitude is Not worth it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We apologize for this experience and have address it with that days staff. I'm so sorry this happened, especially on your first time visiting us. We strive to make all our customers feel important and to leave with a smile. We apologize again and hope you will give us another try.

reviews_data.review_text: I used to love going here. The coffee is very good. Unfortunately, we will not be going back. Went today through the drive thru and ordered my usual large coffee. I went for the first time this morning with high expectations, I was extremely disappointed save will not return,  I arrived at 6am at opening, it was the only customer and it took 13 minutes to get my order, I only ordered and iced coffee, nothing else and paid over $3 for a coffee half the size if a McDonalds coffe I'd pay $1 for on the app, im fine with paying more for a premium product but the girl making my coffee simply poured hot coffee over ice and added cream , what I got was extremely watered down and tasted like rust from the dirty looking metal cup yhe worker used to stir it so that the plastic cup didn't mt when she poured hot coffee over ice.  During my 12 minute wait I watched yhe employees clumsily and slowly set up for business setting iut what looked too be days old grocery store bought pastries marked up to fresh bakery prices.  Its a good thing your salvation comes from the grace of God and not your business.  Terrible place, Ill never return . Its ok to be a Christian business, its not ok to use your faith to get business out of your beliefs if your product is poor.

Came to the Holy Grind this morning for the first time. Everyone raves about it. After today I'm not sure why. I ordered an iced caramel macchiato with oat milk and the cheese danish. I spent $10 and I tipped a dollar. When she handed me my drink I noticed that the label said whole milk. So I asked her if it did in fact have whole milk that I wont be able to drink it because it will make me sick. And that I had asked for oat milk. She tells me that the label maker just prints it out that way and that it should be fine. I could tell that it was regular milk. As someone who cannot drink it, you definitely notice it when it's in your presence. I told her that I wasn't comfortable with drinking it because if it is in fact whole milk I will get sick. So if she could just please check to make sure. She takes the drink and is gone for a few minutes. Comes back and says I think I fixed it and everything should be fine now, and tells me again it's just the way that the printer prints out the label. The drink that she gives me looks extremely watered down. I take one sip and it just tastes like water. My theory (because I didn't see what she did with my drink) is that she took my drink, dumped out the whole milk and then filled it with water. I was so disappointed. I just ended up leaving. Can't tell you how the Danish is as I still haven't eaten it yet. I feel like the concern for the wrong type of milk being put in wasn't taken very seriously and I wish that they would have just made things right by remaking the drink the right way. Now I am out $11 and wasted a 40 minute drive.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello thank you for making us aware of this. We apologize for your first time with us not being the best it could have been. We spoke with the employees working this morning about this. Your first drink was made incorrectly and they did remake the drink for you with the oat milk that you asked for. I don't know why it would have tasted watered down. But regardless, we are going to refund your purchase back to you and we hope you will give us another chance to make a better impression than this time. We take milk options very seriously because one of our owners has to have almond milk in her drinks.

I'd recommend trying The Holy Grind Coffee House

reviews_data.review_text: I got the Conquest of Canaan. Best cup of coffee I've had. Will be back.
Amazing staff!! They are always in a happy mood! I love the back-ground music, and the "Jesus Loves You" written on the side of the cup! That always makes me smile! And the coffee is wonderful!

I love the Holy Grind. The shop itself is lovely and soothing with multiple areas to sit, to talk, and to just enjoy your coffee.  I have seen people in there meeting for Bible studies, people doing work, people chatting and some just reading.  The people behind the counter are always nice and they make some great drinks.  I personally love the frozen drinks like the Red Velvet and the Snickerdoodle drinks.  They have smoothies, little pastries, and speciality drinks for the season. Came to the Holy Grind this morning for the first time. Everyone raves about it. After today I'm not sure why. I ordered an iced caramel macchiato with oat milk and the cheese danish. So I asked her if it did in fact have whole milk that I wont be able to drink it because it will make me sick. And that I had asked for oat milk. She tells me that the label maker just prints it out that way and that it should be fine. I could tell that it was regular milk. As someone who cannot drink it, you definitely notice it when it's in your presence. I told her that I wasn't comfortable with drinking it because if it is in fact whole milk I will get sick. So if she could just please check to make sure. She takes the drink and is gone for a few minutes. Comes back and says I think I fixed it and everything should be fine now, and tells me again it's just the way that the printer prints out the label. The drink that she gives me looks extremely watered down. I take one sip and it just tastes like water. My theory (because I didn't see what she did with my drink) is that she took my drink, dumped out the whole milk and then filled it with water. I was so disappointed. I just ended up leaving. Can't tell you how the Danish is as I still haven't eaten it yet. I feel like the concern for the wrong type of milk being put in wasn't taken very seriously and I wish that they would have just made things right by remaking the drink the right way. Now I am out $11 and wasted a 40 minute drive.
